A PDF (Portable Document Format) file is a file format
developed by Adobe
in 1992 to present documents, including text formatting
and images, in a manner independent of application software
, hardware, and operating systems.
It is based on the PostScript language and is a widely used
format for exchanging and archiving documents.
PDF files can contain a variety of content, including text,
vector graphics,raster images, and interactive elements
such as links and forms.
They can also include metadata,
such as document information and tags,to provide additional
context and accessibility features.
PDF files can be encrypted and digitally signed for security and
authentication purposes
